  <\question>
    For the circuit in Figure 1:

    <\padded-center>
      <image|<tuple|<#>|png>|0.4par|0.3par||>

      Figure 1.
    </padded-center>

    <\enumerate-numeric-bracket>
      <item>Use Nodal analysis to find <math|u<rsub|1>>.

      <item>Find the power associated with the current source, and determine whether it is absorbing or supplying energy.
    </enumerate-numeric-bracket>
  </question>

  \ 

  <\question>
    \ For the circuit in Figure 2:

    <\padded-center>
      <with|par-mode|center|<image|<tuple|<#>|png>|0.6par|0.25par||>>

      Figure 2.
    </padded-center>

    <\enumerate-numeric-bracket>
      <item>Find Thevenin's equivalent circuit between terminal a, b <math|<around*|(|without R<rsub|x>|)>>.

      <item>Determine the value of <math|R<rsub|x>> that results in maximum power transfer to <math|R<rsub|x>>, and calculate that maximum power.
    </enumerate-numeric-bracket>
  </question>

  <\question>
    For the ciruit in Figure 3:

    <\padded-center>
      <image|<tuple|<#>|png>|0.8par|0.207545par||>

      Figure 3.
    </padded-center>

    All the operational amplifiers is ideal and operates in linear region. Find <math|i<rsub|o> >in the circuit.
  </question>

