  <\question>
    For the circuit in Figure 4:

    <\padded-center>
      <image|<tuple|<#>|png>|0.6par|0.22par||>

      Figure 4
    </padded-center>

    The operational amplifier is ideal and operates in linear region. Find <math|U<rsub|o>> in the circuit.
  </question>

  \;

  <\question>
    For the circuit in Figure 5, the expression <math|V<rsub|s><around*|(|t|)>> for the voltage source follows:

    <\equation*>
      V<rsub|s><around*|(|t|)>=<choice|<tformat|<table|<row|<cell|6t+15 V,0\<leqslant\>t\<leqslant\>0.5s>>|<row|<cell|18V,0\<gtr\>0.5s>>>>>
    </equation*>

    Assume the system reaches steady state before t = 0. The switch has been opened long enough before t = 0s, and it is closed at t = 0s.\ 

    <\padded-center>
      <image|<tuple|<#>|png>|0.5par|0.2par||><image|<tuple|<#>|png>|0.25par|0.2par||>

      Figure 5
    </padded-center>

    <\enumerate-numeric-bracket>
      <item>Find <math|V<rsub|c><around*|(|t|)>> for <math|t\<gtr\>0>.

      <item>When <math|t\<rightarrow\>+\<infty\>>, find the energy stored in capacitor.
    </enumerate-numeric-bracket>
  </question>

  \;

  <\question>
    For the circuit in Figure 6:\ 

